# Frontend rules — {{project_name}}

## Boundaries
- No inline styles; use the project's design token system
- No direct DOM manipulation outside of framework primitives
- All user inputs validated before submission, not only on error return
- Every interactive element has a keyboard equivalent and ARIA label where needed

## Naming
- Components: `PascalCase`
- Files: `kebab-case.tsx`
- Event handlers: `on` + PascalCase verb (`onClick`, `onSubmit`)

## State
- Prefer local component state; lift only when siblings genuinely share it
- No client-side state for data that belongs on the server
- Derived values are computed, not stored

## Structure
- One component per file
- Keep components under ~150 lines; extract rather than grow
- Data fetching lives at route/page level, not in leaf components

---
_Extend these rules with project-specific conventions as the codebase grows._
